1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,040
 You know, we're in our final week of public faith, what it means to live the gospel in

2
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:06,400
 the world around us.

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:10,040
 And, you know, as a group of pastors, as we were praying a number of months ago for this

4
00:00:10,040 --> 00:00:14,220
 series and we were asking, "What are the topics that's on the Lord's heart?"

5
00:00:14,220 --> 00:00:17,800
 This one came up that we're speaking about today, and we're like, "We can't do a series

6
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:22,000
 on how we live the gospel publicly if we don't talk about the reality of our resources in

7
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:28,440
 our lives and the way in which we operate with the resources that God has given us."

8
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:33,480
 The reality is that one of the most public ways that you will reveal the gospel to the

9
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:38,800
 world around you is how you steward the resources that are in your life.

10
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:44,480
 So whether that's your time, whether that's your energy, whether that's your finances,

11
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:50,480
 whether that's your talents or your gifts, what you do with what you've been given reveals

12
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:56,520
 to the world the inner values and commitments that you hold.

13
00:00:56,520 --> 00:01:00,040
 It's always been said, right, that if you want to find out what's important to someone,

14
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:04,240
 just do an audit of what they spend their time and their money on.

15
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:08,820
 That'll show you pretty quickly what is in the heart and the life of someone.

16
00:01:08,820 --> 00:01:13,120
 But I think for us Christians, this area of our resources and what we do with them is

17
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:19,780
 not just an audit of kind of the values within us, it's actually a question of discipleship.

18
00:01:19,780 --> 00:01:23,880
 It's actually an invitation into discipleship.

19
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:27,880
 Because what we do with the resources that we have over a period of time as Christians

20
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:32,400
 will become the barometer of our relationship with Jesus.

21
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:36,920
 And over time, it will show the people within our community, the people outside of that

22
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:46,060
 community, the level of submission, the level of honor, the level of obedience that we have

23
00:01:46,060 --> 00:01:50,040
 to the one that we seek to proclaim.

24
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:56,120
 The stewardship of your resources is perhaps the greatest way you reveal to the world around

25
00:01:56,120 --> 00:02:02,880
 you the love that you have for a God who has saved, redeemed, and restored you.

26
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:07,680
 There are so many passages in Scripture that speak about this idea of stewarding the resources

27
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,800
 God has given us.

28
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:12,680
 But I want to go to one today that is from the apostle Peter.

29
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,320
 And he's writing to the church.

30
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,320
 This is his first letter.

31
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:19,480
 And he's writing to his church in a time of persecution, a time when the church is struggling

32
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:23,680
 and he writes to them and says, "You've got to understand that you've been saved not just

33
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:27,720
 for your little gatherings that you have in your house churches, but you've been saved

34
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:34,440
 to bring the message of Christ, the hope of Jesus, into the world around you."

35
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:37,760
 And he has this list of ways in which we do that.

36
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:43,200
 And embedded in the middle of it is just this one verse where he speaks specifically about

37
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,680
 the resources in our lives.

38
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:49,260
 Let me read this to you from 1 Peter 4, starting in verse 10.

39
00:02:49,260 --> 00:02:54,720
 He says, "Each one of you should use whatever gift that you have received to serve others,

40
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:59,440
 being faithful stewards of God's grace in its various form."

41
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:05,440
 I love what Peter does here, a very simple sentence, a very simple verse.

42
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:09,160
 But he starts by saying this, "Each one of you should use whatever gift that you have

43
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:10,720
 received to serve others."

44
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:14,920
 So his starting point is every single one of us has received a gift.

45
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:18,680
 He doesn't say, "Those of you that think you're gifted."

46
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:22,640
 He doesn't say, "Those of you that are wealthy and know that you have a lot of resource."

47
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:28,960
 He says, "Each one of you, regardless of whether you think you have an abundance or not, should

48
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:36,240
 use what it is that God has given you for His glory, to serve the people around you."

49
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:39,760
 Which is deeply challenging because I think as Christians, when we think about the resources

50
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:43,240
 in our lives, we have two issues.

51
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:48,320
 We first of all think either we have a lot, and that can lead us into a place of pride,

52
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:52,840
 or we look at the neighbor next to us and we compare ourselves and we find jealousy

53
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:56,700
 in us because we think we don't have as much as them.

54
00:03:56,700 --> 00:04:01,680
 So when we begin to think about resources in our lives, often our starting point is

55
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:04,580
 either pride or it's jealousy.

56
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:10,200
 It's either I've got what I need or it's kind of comparative or comparison to the one next

57
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:11,200
 to me.

58
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:15,720
 And Peter starts this topic by cutting through all of that, and he's like, "It's not about

59
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:20,920
 how much you have, it's about what you do with what you have been given.

60
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:24,280
 And each one of you has been given something.

61
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:29,720
 And each one of you should administer whatever it is that you've been given to serve the

62
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:32,960
 people around you."

63
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:36,260
 Notice the language he uses in this verse to highlight this.

64
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:37,760
 He says gift.

65
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,720
 He uses the word received.

66
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,980
 Later on in the verse, he says God's grace.

67
00:04:42,980 --> 00:04:48,800
 These words are words specifically that Peter is using to help you to understand that there

68
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:54,920
 is a significant mindset shift that you need when you become a Christian when it comes

69
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,120
 to the resources in your life.

70
00:04:57,120 --> 00:05:03,480
 He says you've got to understand that this is a gift, that you have received it, and

71
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:06,040
 you've received it by God's grace.

72
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:10,240
 So fundamentally what Peter is teaching here to the church is that you've got to understand

73
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:14,120
 that God is the owner of all things.

74
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,120
 They're all his.

75
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:17,160
 He is sovereign.

76
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,480
 He's powerful.

77
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:23,300
 He has control of everything in this world, and everything you have is a gift.

78
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:25,200
 You haven't earned it.

79
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:28,960
 It's not like he's looked down on the vine today and gone, "Oh, Pastor Andrew, he's in

80
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:29,960
 a good place right now.

81
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,320
 I'm going to give him a little bit more."

82
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:39,000
 This is a gift received by God's grace because he is the owner of all things, and that is

83
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:42,160
 a deeply important thing for us to be aware of.

84
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,640
 Let me say it in reverse.

85
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:45,360
 We are not owners.

86
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:47,840
 Come on, church.

87
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:53,480
 We are not owners, which is weird because before we come to Christ, that's exactly the

88
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:55,720
 mindset that we have.

89
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:59,560
 Before we have this relationship with Jesus, our mindset is always going to be, "I work

90
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,560
 hard.

91
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:01,560
 I gain.

92
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,560
 I earn.

93
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,560
 I control.

94
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:08,440
 It is mine, and I get to do what I want with it."

95
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:13,080
 And so our mindset before we come in a relationship with Jesus is, "I'm the owner of everything

96
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,760
 that I've worked hard for."

97
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:18,080
 But actually, when we come into faith with Jesus, the Bible does not give us an option

98
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,760
 to think that way anymore.

99
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:23,600
 The Bible says it's all a 180-degree thought.

100
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:27,480
 Now no longer am I the owner of everything that I've worked hard for.

101
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:33,520
 Now I'm a servant of the one who has done it all, that it is all in his hands.

102
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,520
 He owns it all.

103
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:38,440
 And my relationship now is not, "This is mine because I've gained."

104
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:41,920
 It is, "This is his, so what do I do with it?"

105
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:44,440
 Are you with me?

106
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:50,360
 We are not masters of our lives and owners of the things we have through our own hard

107
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,200
 work.

108
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:59,400
 We are servants of the King and stewards of his resources through his divine grace, and

109
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:02,160
 that changes everything.

110
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,480
 That challenges us.

111
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:11,560
 That should light a fire within us, that we would begin to think of our resources in a

112
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,640
 different way.

113
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:20,280
 Rather than thinking that we have the responsibility because we own, we begin to think, "What is

114
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:28,860
 it that Jesus would want me to do with this because it's not mine anyway?"

115
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:36,200
 When your posture of stewardship is to say, "It's not mine anyway," the kingdom of God

116
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:39,000
 advances.

117
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,120
 This is why Peter uses this word here.

118
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:45,640
 He says, "You are a faithful steward."

119
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:48,840
 The word in the Greek is oikonomos.

120
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:52,160
 Oikonomos literally translated, oikos is house.

121
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:55,120
 Onomos is this idea of being a servant.

122
00:07:55,120 --> 00:08:01,920
 So oikonomos is basically someone who in the first century was a household manager, a household

123
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:02,920
 administrator.

124
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:08,500
 I think it's profound that Peter took this word from the first century that everybody

125
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:14,340
 would have understood as an oikonomos is a household manager, and he applies it to the

126
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:16,880
 resources that we have in our life from God.

127
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:21,840
 He says, "Don't you realize because he's the owner of all things, he's done this profound

128
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:22,840
 thing.

129
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:30,720
 He's called you to be his household manager, to manage and administrate his resources,

130
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:33,960
 which if I was God, I would not have done it that way."

131
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,760
 I mean, stop for a moment and think about that, right?

132
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:39,560
 Like if you're God and you're like, "Well, I have all this stuff in my life.

133
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:43,280
 I have all this power and I want to give it away," and you look at the human beings, you'd

134
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:46,800
 be like, "I'm not giving it to those people," right?

135
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:51,760
 You'd be like, "The sin, the brokenness, the pride, the arrogance."

136
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:57,040
 But God in his wisdom, a wisdom that we don't always understand, says, "No, I've placed

137
00:08:57,040 --> 00:09:02,200
 all of my resources into your hands because you are my economists.

138
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:07,800
 I want you to now work that resource out into the world around you."

139
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:12,560
 Notice that the oikonomos word sounds a lot like a modern word we use today, which is

140
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,040
 the word economy.

141
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:20,080
 But actually, the word economy draws from this Greek word oikonomos.

142
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:24,220
 So what Peter's teaching is, you've got to understand that when you come to faith in

143
00:09:24,220 --> 00:09:28,520
 Christ Jesus and you look at all the resources in your life, you are then swept up in a new

144
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,520
 economy.

145
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:35,420
 It's not the old economy where you can hoard and receive and do what you want with it.

146
00:09:35,420 --> 00:09:36,420
 It's a new economy.

147
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:42,720
 And in God's economy, he's looking for his people to release that there would be a flow

148
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:46,200
 of that resource in the kingdom.

149
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:51,480
 This concept of the flow of resource is central to the idea of what it means for us to be

150
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:58,920
 stewards and household managers, and that we are to do this in beautiful kingdom revealing

151
00:09:58,920 --> 00:10:00,720
 ways.

152
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:05,160
 This is the image of the first church, is it not, in the book of Acts, who as they begin

153
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:10,920
 to wrestle with the profundity of Jesus' death and resurrection, begin to create communities

154
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:17,240
 all around the Greco-Roman empire that would reveal the gospel, reveal a new economy to

155
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,240
 the world around it.

156
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:22,200
 I mean, take a look at Acts chapter 2, verses 44 and 45.

157
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,200
 It says this.

158
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:28,400
 It says, "All the believers were together and had everything in common.

159
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:32,800
 They sold property and possessions to give to anyone who had need."

160
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,600
 This is a new economy at work.

161
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:39,040
 And it's at work because these Christians have begun to understand they're no longer

162
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:41,080
 the owners, but they are stewards.

163
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:45,880
 And because they're stewards, then the flow of those resources needs to move out from

164
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:50,520
 them into the world around them.

165
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:56,840
 Anybody who had need within their community was met through the flow of God's stewards

166
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:57,920
 within the church.

167
00:10:57,920 --> 00:11:00,240
 Such a beautiful picture.

168
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:03,320
 And think about the implications of this.

169
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:09,760
 Abundance, this generosity, which is really the overflow of the resources of God in the

170
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:16,800
 world, and poverty, which is the restriction of those resources and actually the inequitable

171
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:25,960
 distribution of them, both generosity and poverty flow from the gateway of stewardship.

172
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:32,480
 Which means that if we are the economists of God's household, we as Christians are responsible

173
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:36,960
 for whether there might be a generous flow of those resources in our communities or there

174
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:42,680
 might be a poverty type restriction of those resources in our communities.

175
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:47,040
 And we're not just talking about the church, we're talking about our city.

176
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:54,280
 And as we take on board that incredible responsibility, it should shake something within us.

177
00:11:54,280 --> 00:12:00,720
 It's why Peter says here, "You are to use this economic gift that you have to flow those

178
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:04,240
 resources to serve others."

179
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:09,320
 Now that doesn't mean that you can't be a steward of those resources in a way that can

180
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:15,640
 benefit yourself, but the Bible is trying to challenge us to think about this idea of

181
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:22,640
 generosity and poverty and which of these two do I generally do in the world around

182
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:23,640
 me.

183
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:30,680
 In other words, am I flowing the resource as a river or have I become a dam?

184
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:34,080
 Have I backed up those resources?

185
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:41,240
 Are those resources building up behind the walls of my fear, the walls of my pride, the

186
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:44,000
 walls of my greed?

187
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:49,880
 Have I become a dam for the flow of God's resources in the world or am I a river which

188
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:55,600
 is releasing and watering the world around me with the beautiful things that Christ has

189
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:58,440
 done for me?

190
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,880
 This is a deep challenge.

191
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:03,880
 And this is why Peter says these words.

192
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:09,720
 He says, "You're not just a steward, but you must be a faithful steward."

193
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:13,640
 Peter understood that a stewardship mentality is not enough.

194
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:19,400
 You have to steward with a faithfulness, with this sense that you understand what is on

195
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:24,200
 God's heart and you want to administer that in the world so that the gospel might be revealed.

196
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:30,440
 You see, just having a stewardship mentality does not guarantee that you will become a

197
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:33,800
 vessel of the flow of God's resources in the world.

198
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:39,120
 You got to take that mentality and link it to this idea of faithfulness.

199
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:41,640
 And faithfulness I think is linked to two things.

200
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:47,160
 First of all, it's linked to the idea of being obedient with what God has given us.

201
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:50,000
 It doesn't mean that you have to take a vow of poverty.

202
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:54,600
 Being faithful to the stewardship of God's resources in your life might mean taking care

203
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,880
 of your family, making sure your family has what it needs.

204
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:01,320
 It's not saying that you have to become poor.

205
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:04,760
 But equally, it's not saying that you have to become rich.

206
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:08,720
 It's not saying that suddenly as a good faithful steward, God's going to keep rewarding you

207
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:11,440
 and rewarding you and rewarding you so you can become wealthier and wealthier.

208
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:16,080
 This is not a prosperity gospel-centered idea.

209
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:23,040
 In fact, what Peter is saying is whether you're poor or you're wealthy, God is saying the

210
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:25,840
 same thing to you.

211
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:30,720
 God speaks exactly the same thing to the poorest of the poor and the wealthiest of the wealthy.

212
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,480
 He asks them the same question.

213
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,480
 Here's the question.

214
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:37,840
 Are you being faithful with the resource that God has given you?

215
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:42,880
 You see, faithfulness is not linked to abundance.

216
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:44,840
 It's linked to obedience.

217
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:52,680
 And so those who don't seem to have much and those that seem to have a lot are asked that

218
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:57,000
 question, "Are we still being faithful with what it is that we have received?

219
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:03,440
 Are we flowing the resource that God has placed within us?"

220
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:09,720
 This is why when the Bible speaks about the resources that he gives to his church, it

221
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,360
 doesn't speak about it primarily as a theoretical issue.

222
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:16,040
 It's not spoken about primarily as a theological issue.

223
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:19,400
 It's spoken primarily as a relational issue.

224
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:27,080
 In other words, my relationship with the owner of all things will have a direct dependency

225
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:34,000
 on how I steward those resources, how I see Jesus is going to impact what I do with his

226
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,000
 resources.

227
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,200
 Does that make sense?

228
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:42,520
 So as my intimacy and my knowledge and my connection with Jesus increases, so should

229
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:47,800
 the resources of him flow out from me in ways that reveal the gospel around me.

230
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:54,780
 But equally, if that relationship is stale, if it's become stagnant, if it's broken because

231
00:15:54,780 --> 00:16:01,600
 of sin or broken because of whatever it might be, then I don't become a vessel by which

232
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:06,960
 I might be able to use those resources in the way that would honor the owner.

233
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:11,160
 This is exactly the teaching that Jesus gives us in the parable of the talent in Matthew

234
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:12,840
 25 verses 14 to 30.

235
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:17,160
 We don't have time to look at it line by line today, but let me just summarize the parable

236
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,240
 itself.

237
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:24,120
 There is a wealthy homeowner who's going on a trip and actually gives his property to

238
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:30,960
 be cared for in his absence to three oikonomists in his midst, household managers.

239
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:35,680
 Two of them take what is received from the master of the house, and they put that money

240
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,000
 to work.

241
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,000
 They know him.

242
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,200
 They know what he would want.

243
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:42,320
 They understand his expectations, and they put that money to work.

244
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:47,240
 And when the master of the house returns, they show, "Look, we've doubled what it is

245
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:49,600
 that you have given us."

246
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:53,440
 And the household master looks at what they've done, knowing that it is in connection to

247
00:16:53,440 --> 00:17:00,720
 his character, and speaks over them, "Well done, my good and faithful servants."

248
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:06,800
 "You've proven a faithfulness because you knew me."

249
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:12,400
 The third oikonomist, though, didn't know the master very well, and in fact was only

250
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:16,760
 afraid of the master, so fearful, in fact, that he was like, "Well, if I invest this

251
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:19,640
 money and I get it wrong and I lose the money, then I'm going to get punished."

252
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:24,720
 So he takes the gift that he had been given, buries it in the ground, just waiting for

253
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,040
 the master to return.

254
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:29,320
 When the master returns, uncovers it, and brings it to the master.

255
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:31,800
 And the master's like, "What have you done?"

256
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,200
 And the response is, "Well, I thought you were like this.

257
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,200
 I feared you.

258
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:38,000
 I thought you were going to tell me off if I got it wrong."

259
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:42,280
 And the master's like, "You have no idea who I am, because if you knew my character, if

260
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:46,260
 you knew my heart, you would have at least put it into the bank and earned some interest

261
00:17:46,260 --> 00:17:47,260
 on it."

262
00:17:47,260 --> 00:17:49,320
 He literally says that.

263
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:52,560
 And he says, "So therefore," he doesn't say, "Well done, my good and faithful servant."

264
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:53,560
 He says, "No, no."

265
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:57,280
 And actually, there's some of the things that he says are pretty strong in the Scripture.

266
00:17:57,280 --> 00:18:02,980
 And it's like he gets sort of chastised because he didn't know him.

267
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:06,840
 And so when Peter is speaking to the church about this idea of, "Hey, you're a faithful

268
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:10,280
 steward of the resources God has given you," I think he's thinking about the parable of

269
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:11,280
 talents.

270
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:14,040
 And he's saying, "That means you've got to know the one who is the owner of it all.

271
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:20,960
 And as your heart increases in that, your hands will open even more."

272
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:25,440
 The more that we understand the heart and the nature of God, the more we will be faithful

273
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:27,720
 with the resources that He has given us.

274
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:31,060
 That's just the reality of it all.

275
00:18:31,060 --> 00:18:32,660
 So how do we do this?

276
00:18:32,660 --> 00:18:38,920
 How do we as Christians honor the owner of all things with the faithfulness of a stewardship

277
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:43,920
 of the resources that He's placed in our lives, whether those resources may seem to us a lot

278
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:45,000
 or a little?

279
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,000
 How do we do it faithfully?

280
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:51,320
 Well, there's this beautiful passage in the Old Testament, in the book of Ecclesiastes,

281
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,320
 actually.

282
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:55,680
 And oftentimes when I've spoken on stewardship, I've gone to this passage.

283
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:58,960
 So if you've been at the Vine for a while, you're probably going to roll your eyes now

284
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,520
 because I'm going back to that passage again.

285
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:07,480
 But I think it's actually one of the most beautiful demonstrations of what stewardship

286
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:12,680
 of resource really looks like and what Peter is teaching about in 1 Peter 4.10.

287
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:18,680
 So this is Ecclesiastes chapter 4, a wisdom writer who's writing truths about the world.

288
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:20,640
 And he says this.

289
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:25,400
 He says, "The fool folds his hands and ruins himself.

290
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:31,040
 Better one handful with tranquility than two handfuls with toil and chasing after the wind."

291
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:36,400
 It's classic wisdom, kind of poetic structure to this verse.

292
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:39,320
 The writer is challenging his people.

293
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:43,120
 The broader context of the chapter is he's talking specifically about what we have, the

294
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,960
 resources in our lives.

295
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:47,880
 He says, "The fool folds his hands.

296
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:53,760
 Better one handful with tranquility than two handfuls with toil and chasing after the wind."

297
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:58,360
 Let me show you a bit of a demonstration of what I think actually the wisdom writer here

298
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:04,040
 is trying to communicate through the Hebrew word that is used here in the structure of

299
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:05,600
 the passage.

300
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:08,000
 So I want you to think this is a box of rice.

301
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:13,100
 I want you to think about this box of rice as the resources in your life, like your energy,

302
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:17,240
 your time, your finances, your talents, your gifts, whatever they might be.

303
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:22,440
 This represents the fullness of those resources that God has given to you.

304
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:28,000
 The wisdom writer says, "You're a fool," the Hebrew means you're basically an idiot, "if

305
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:32,600
 you recognize that you have all these resources and you fold your hands to them."

306
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:36,560
 In other words, you don't do anything with it.

307
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:41,160
 This is the posture of that third servant in the parable of the talents.

308
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:45,680
 It's like I've got all this resource that has been given to me, but I just fold my hands

309
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:50,120
 and I check out and I don't do anything with it.

310
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:52,200
 You might be sitting there thinking like, "Well, that's a bit silly.

311
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:55,860
 Why would anyone ever not do something with what they have been given?"

312
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:59,960
 But I wonder whether you just take a moment to reflect about why maybe all of us at some

313
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:04,880
 point folds our hands to the resources God has given us.

314
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:10,060
 I think we fold our hands sometimes out of fear, fear that if we did something with those

315
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:15,120
 resources we might lose them entirely and we don't want to lose them.

316
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:17,840
 So we fold our hands and check out.

317
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:21,880
 I think sometimes we fold our hands because maybe in the past we did something with our

318
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:27,220
 resource, maybe our energy or our time or we connected in a relationship or we gave

319
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:32,700
 everything to someone and they turned their back on us, they betrayed us or they hurt

320
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:33,700
 us deeply.

321
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:38,800
 And because of that hurt and that pain, we're like, "I'm never going to do that again.

322
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:42,520
 I'm never going to give anybody my time like that again."

323
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:47,080
 And so out of hurt, we fold our hands.

324
00:21:47,080 --> 00:21:50,240
 I think the other reason why we do it is out of insecurity.

325
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:55,600
 We compare our gifts, our resources to what somebody else has and we think, "Well, the

326
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:59,840
 church doesn't need that gift of mine because have you seen that person?"

327
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:03,720
 Or "My talent doesn't seem to be as great as that," or "My resources are not as much."

328
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:09,960
 And so because of an insecurity that's driven by comparison, we fold our hands.

329
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:15,600
 The wisdom writer says, "If you're doing that, you're an idiot."

330
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,480
 But then he says this.

331
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:22,360
 He says, "You're also a bit of an idiot if you take two handfuls."

332
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:26,240
 He says, "Two handfuls is a toil and a chasing after the wind."

333
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:30,120
 In the Hebrew, the word for hand in this part of the passage is actually the Hebrew word

334
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:36,600
 "khofen," and "khofen" means literally to clench your hand, to grasp a hold of.

335
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:42,360
 So the wisdom writer is saying, "You are also a fool if you grasp a hold of those resources

336
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,200
 and you hold onto them as tightly as you can.

337
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:48,000
 You khofen the resource."

338
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:51,280
 Now on the surface, we look at this and we think, "But isn't that a good thing?"

339
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:52,720
 I mean, we haven't folded our hands.

340
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,040
 We haven't checked out.

341
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:59,040
 We've taken the resource that God has given us and we're holding it tightly.

342
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:00,160
 And sometimes I think we kid ourselves.

343
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:04,320
 It's like, "I'm holding it tightly until God tells me to do something with it."

344
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:07,760
 But actually we're just hoping that God never speaks to us and that we can just continue

345
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:12,440
 to hold on to the two great handfuls of resource that we've got.

346
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:13,840
 I want you to notice two things.

347
00:23:13,840 --> 00:23:18,680
 Number one, it's really hard when you're grasping a hold of the resources God has given you

348
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:24,200
 in your life like khofen to get more of that resource into your hands.

349
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:28,600
 I mean, I'd have to change the posture of my hand to be able to do so.

350
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:31,320
 Notice also that it's hard to let it flow.

351
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:37,280
 If I grasp it tightly, it's not falling out of my hands perhaps like it should.

352
00:23:37,280 --> 00:23:43,760
 The wisdom writer is saying, "The posture of this is toil and chasing after the wind."

353
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,560
 This is anxiety and stress.

354
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:48,520
 This is a poverty mentality.

355
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:50,440
 I'm not going to lose what it is.

356
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:52,280
 I don't want to lose what I've got.

357
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:56,960
 And in the stress and the toil, we grasp a hold even tighter.

358
00:23:56,960 --> 00:24:04,520
 And we say things like, "When my bank account gets to this level, I'll be more generous."

359
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:10,560
 And then when we get there, we're like, "Yeah, but I just got more expenses now as well.

360
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:14,600
 So maybe it's okay for me to wait again."

361
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:20,520
 I think all of us resonate with the stress and the anxiety and the toil of khofen.

362
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:25,860
 We may have two big handfuls, but it's killing us.

363
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:29,440
 So the wisdom writer is saying, "There's a better way to posture your heart when it

364
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:31,800
 comes to the resources of God's kingdom."

365
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:36,480
 He says, "It's better to have just one handful, but with tranquility."

366
00:24:36,480 --> 00:24:39,320
 The Hebrew word for handful here is chof.

367
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:45,520
 Chof literally means an open hand, a palm facing upwards.

368
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:50,800
 So rather than these two grasping hands of posture of heart, he's saying, "It's better

369
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:52,680
 to be like this.

370
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:57,280
 It's better to have one hand open before him like this."

371
00:24:57,280 --> 00:25:02,760
 Now you'll notice that the resources is flowing just like Peter would hope that it would flow.

372
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:05,760
 But if you're anything like me, you're seeing the resources coming out of your bank account

373
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:08,200
 or out of your energy, and you're like, "Hang on a sec.

374
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:11,720
 There's not a lot of resource left."

375
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:15,840
 But notice what happens when your posture is like this, God can do this.

376
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:19,280
 Because God can put in and flow and in and flow.

377
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,720
 And this, my friends, is the flow of the kingdom.

378
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:24,480
 This is what the resources are supposed to do.

379
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:29,960
 The Bible writer says, "Oh man, it is better to be like this and to have tranquility in

380
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:34,640
 your life, receiving and flowing, receiving and flowing."

381
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:40,320
 Peter writes to the church and he says, "Be a faithful steward of God's grace that he's

382
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:41,320
 given to you.

383
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:44,840
 It is not to fold and give up, to grasp tightly.

384
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:49,800
 It is literally to just be open-handed before him."

385
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:53,160
 This, my friends, is peace.

386
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,920
 It's life.

387
00:25:54,920 --> 00:26:02,240
 It's the way God's economy was always designed to be.

388
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:06,960
 A few weeks ago, we were having a staff devotion and somebody shared a story, a testimony of

389
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,840
 one of our community members here at the Vine.

390
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:13,440
 And I was so blown away by this that I was like, "We have to make space in our service

391
00:26:13,440 --> 00:26:15,120
 today to hear of this."

392
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:20,360
 Because it's a story about the flow of God's resources within its kingdom.

393
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:25,080
 So I wonder whether you'd put your hands together as we invite Pastor Stephen and Minaj to come

394
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,080
 to the stage.

395
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:34,360
 Can we do that?

396
00:26:34,360 --> 00:26:42,400
 >> Thanks, Andrew.

397
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,400
 Good morning, everybody.

398
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:49,560
 Just before we start, I just want to just clarify something.

399
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:53,600
 A lot of people are a little bit confused about what's ARISE and what's BOH.

400
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:55,160
 So I just want to clarify that.

401
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:58,240
 So ARISE is a ministry in the Vine Church.

402
00:26:58,240 --> 00:27:03,200
 BOH is an NGO that operates alongside the Vine Church.

403
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:07,120
 We serve a part of the same community.

404
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:12,280
 But the way we kind of figure out who does what in taking care of kind of a holistic

405
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:19,480
 perspective of meeting everybody's needs, BOH focuses on the hand needs, the felt needs,

406
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:21,960
 and we focus on the heart needs, the spiritual needs.

407
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:28,600
 So just to clarify that a little bit, I know a lot of people think ARISE is BOH or BOH

408
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:31,560
 is ARISE, but actually we're two separate things.

409
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:32,560
 So welcome, Minaj.

410
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:36,200
 Good to have you with us today.

411
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:40,720
 I wonder, I know you've been in Hong Kong and around the Vine for about 10 years.

412
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:47,720
 Can you maybe just give us a brief introduction to your background and how you got here?

413
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,560
 Yes.

414
00:27:49,560 --> 00:28:04,560
 I'm originally from India and I grew up in a very strict Hindu family.

415
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:15,280
 And in my early 20s, I believed in science rather than God.

416
00:28:15,280 --> 00:28:30,560
 And due to some trouble in my country, I had to come to Hong Kong as an asylum seeker.

417
00:28:30,560 --> 00:28:43,280
 So after I arrived in Hong Kong, like two weeks, one of my friends invited me to the

418
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:47,040
 Vine church.

419
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:53,440
 It was a Sunday, so I had nothing else to do.

420
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:56,320
 So I say, "Let's go."

421
00:28:56,320 --> 00:29:18,840
 So one of my first visits, I came up for the prayer and the person asked me what I wanted

422
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:22,020
 to pray for.

423
00:29:22,020 --> 00:29:35,200
 So even though at that time I had many material needs, but I found myself asking that, "Please

424
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:42,240
 pray for me to come closer to God."

425
00:29:42,240 --> 00:30:05,180
 And every time when I come to the Vine, I felt amazing peace, but I had never felt before.

426
00:30:05,180 --> 00:30:13,720
 And later I baptized, I remember my new birthday is 12th of June, 2016.

427
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:15,800
 Wow, that's awesome.

428
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,000
 That's awesome.

429
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:23,140
 So Pastor Andrew's been speaking to us today about stewardship and this idea of God's resources

430
00:30:23,140 --> 00:30:28,760
 are meant to flow through us, kind of being a river or a conduit for His resources rather

431
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:31,600
 than holding onto stuff and being like a dam.

432
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:38,480
 So I know part of your story, there's one incident that happened in your life where

433
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:41,260
 something flowed into your life and God blessed you in a way.

434
00:30:41,260 --> 00:30:45,400
 Can you tell us about that?

435
00:30:45,400 --> 00:31:00,120
 Yes, at the very beginning in Hong Kong, in some reason I lost all my belongings, especially

436
00:31:00,120 --> 00:31:02,080
 my shoes.

437
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:10,160
 One of my friends gave me a trouser, but it was too big, too loose.

438
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:11,160
 I cannot walk.

439
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:17,160
 If I walk a few steps, I need to hold or otherwise I had to adjust.

440
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:30,560
 So in desperation, I went to a nearby shop here to buy a belt to fix it.

441
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:38,920
 I found a nice belt, but I didn't have enough money to buy it.

442
00:31:38,920 --> 00:31:49,440
 I tried to negotiate with the shopkeeper, but the shopkeeper wouldn't budge on the

443
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:52,600
 price.

444
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:55,760
 I was really heartbroken.

445
00:31:55,760 --> 00:32:06,760
 I left the shop and I found myself holding the handrail beside the road.

446
00:32:06,760 --> 00:32:24,280
 I was crying and I closed my eyes and I asked God, "God, how long will you test me?"

447
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:35,800
 The next day, we had an ARISE fellowship.

448
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:48,000
 Unexpectedly, an Indonesian sister approached me with a plastic bag and she handed me the

449
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:54,520
 plastic bag and said, "This is for you."

450
00:32:54,520 --> 00:33:06,600
 When I opened the bag, I was astonished to see inside it was a leather belt inside.

451
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:19,160
 Curiously, I asked, "How do you know I needed a belt?"

452
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:30,440
 She said she was shopping the day before.

453
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:47,040
 Suddenly my face popped up in her mind and she felt that God was prompting her to buy

454
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:53,880
 a belt for me.

455
00:33:53,880 --> 00:34:10,400
 And then, later I found out it was the same time when I cried out to the Lord, asking

456
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:20,760
 for a belt for my problem.

457
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:31,360
 Because this incident profoundly changed me.

458
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:48,640
 I also want to be grateful for how she blessed me, even though she had not much money.

459
00:34:48,640 --> 00:34:55,920
 Because she was like an asylum seeker like me.

460
00:34:55,920 --> 00:35:12,880
 But she was obedient and faithful and her faithfulness also guided me.

461
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:22,600
 I also want to follow her example to bless and help others.

462
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:27,520
 And you've been a tremendous blessing to so many people here at the Vine Church and in

463
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:28,520
 ARISE ministry.

464
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:32,720
 I know that's definitely part of your heart.

465
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:38,240
 But I know there's a very specific thing that the Lord asked you to do, and you've been

466
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:41,040
 doing this for like seven to eight years now.

467
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:46,160
 Can you tell us a little bit about that?

468
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:50,760
 Yes.

469
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:55,720
 The Lord blessed me in many ways.

470
00:35:55,720 --> 00:36:01,920
 So I have received so much from the Lord.

471
00:36:01,920 --> 00:36:09,240
 I was thinking I want to give back.

472
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:24,440
 At the same time, the Branches of Hope launched a campaign to give us a piggy bank.

473
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:25,440
 This piggy bank.

474
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:28,800
 This is Manoj's piggy bank.

475
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:41,000
 To collect the changes and bring at the end of the year to donate to BOH.

476
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:44,960
 But I want to participate.

477
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:53,760
 I am thinking how can I participate?

478
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:58,840
 So I prayed to God and asked, "Please guide me."

479
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:05,640
 And God showed me.

480
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:12,880
 I have decided to put one dollar every day in my piggy bank.

481
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:13,880
 Yeah.

482
00:37:13,880 --> 00:37:17,880
 There's money in there.

483
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:27,340
 So at the end of the year, $365 I gave to the BOH.

484
00:37:27,340 --> 00:37:42,880
 So I must be honest with my... because sometime I had no money to recharge my Octopus card.

485
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:48,800
 So I need to borrow from the piggy bank.

486
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:52,120
 I think we've all been there, right?

487
00:37:52,120 --> 00:38:05,760
 But I always make sure to end of every year, I made like $365.

488
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:10,760
 So I am still doing this day.

489
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:13,320
 So I don't know if you heard the last part.

490
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:18,080
 He said this started in 2018 and he's still doing it today as you can hear.

491
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:19,760
 So thank you so much, Manoj.

492
00:38:19,760 --> 00:38:21,600
 That's such an amazing testimony.

493
00:38:21,600 --> 00:38:26,560
 Yeah, let's give him a round of applause.

494
00:38:26,560 --> 00:38:30,440
 Your faithfulness and your obedience to the Lord is an example to all of us.

495
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:34,760
 So thank you very much for sharing that with us today.

496
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:39,760
 God bless you.

497
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:45,560
 I think the Lord sees something like that and sort of turns to Manoj and says, "Well

498
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:48,520
 done, my good and faithful servant."

499
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:49,520
 Amen.

500
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:56,200
 And Peter, Peter writes to the church and he goes, "Each one of you have a gift and

501
00:38:56,200 --> 00:39:00,280
 you are to faithfully administrate that gift to serve others, being a faithful steward

502
00:39:00,280 --> 00:39:04,800
 of God's grace that has been entrusted to you in all of its forms."

503
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,440
 We're not owners.

504
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:07,600
 We're stewards.

505
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:13,480
 We receive such abundance and we've been given such glorious grace.

506
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:17,680
 Peter would say, "It is in your hands."

507
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:21,800
 The question for us then is, are those hands folded?

508
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:22,800
 Are they clenched?

509
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:23,800
 Are they open?

510
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:26,040
 Can I pray for you?

511
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,440
 Should we stand together?

512
00:39:27,440 --> 00:39:28,440
 Let's pray.

513
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:36,600
 Father, I'm just so grateful for each person in this room and watching online and our overflow

514
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:38,080
 in this moment.

515
00:39:38,080 --> 00:39:42,840
 Lord, you called us to be these stewards of the resources you have planted and placed

516
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:45,280
 in our lives.

517
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:52,960
 What a joy it is to be able to stand before you as not owners, but those responsibly entrusted

518
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:55,040
 as household managers.

519
00:39:55,040 --> 00:40:00,680
 Lord, we pray that we would be able to manage your resources effectively for your glory.

520
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:07,280
 Lord, where fear has gotten away, would you just speak to us?

521
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:14,880
 Lord, where insecurity has played a part in us holding on, would you forgive us?

522
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:21,360
 Lord, for those of us in this room that recognize we've become a dam rather than a flowing river,

523
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:26,720
 would you help us to understand why and would you enable us to let go?

524
00:40:26,720 --> 00:40:33,040
 For those of us that resonate with the two fists clenched and the stress and the fear

525
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:38,360
 and the anxiety that comes alongside of those two clenched fists.

526
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:46,440
 Lord, would your spirit fill us now and bring that tranquility, that peace that needs to

527
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:47,800
 be over us?

528
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:55,400
 And would you help us to open our hand before you, that palm open, enabling the resource

529
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:58,640
 to flow for your kingdom?

530
00:40:58,640 --> 00:41:02,600
 And God, what a beautiful thing it is to be Christians in Hong Kong that could model a

531
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:07,920
 different economy to the world's economy, to Hong Kong's economy.

532
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:12,960
 That it wouldn't be about hoarding and gaining and status and showing.

533
00:41:12,960 --> 00:41:20,440
 It would be about liberating and giving and letting go and glorifying Jesus.

534
00:41:20,440 --> 00:41:26,520
 And as Menage has so beautifully shown us, as he received, so he eagerly gave, would

535
00:41:26,520 --> 00:41:33,740
 that be upon us all as we head out to be those public witnesses of the gospel in the spheres

536
00:41:33,740 --> 00:41:35,400
 of influence you planted us in?

537
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:38,720
 And we give you glory for this in Jesus' name.

538
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:40,520
 Everyone says, "Amen."

539
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:41,520
 Amen.

540
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:41,880
 Let's worship together.

541
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:45,240
 [APPLAUSE]

